'''Christian Kabasele''' (born 24 February 1991) is a Congolese-born Belgian professional [[association football|footballer]] who currently plays as a [[Defender (association football)|defender]] for [[Watford F.C.|Watford]] in the [[Premier League]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=krcgenk.be|title=KRC Genk squad|url=http://www.krcgenk.be/nl/a-kern/spelers|accessdate=}}</ref>
==Club career== Kabasele started his career with [[K.A.S. Eupen|Eupen]].
On 27 January 2011, [[KV Mechelen|Mechelen]] confirmed Kabasele has joined on loan until the end of the season.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.sporza.be/cm/sporza/voetbal/Jupiler_Pro_League/1.951041|publisher=sporza.be|title=KV Mechelen finds solution for striker problem|accessdate=2011-01-27|language=Dutch}}</ref> He made his debut on 12 February in a 3–1 home win against [[K.V.C. Westerlo|Westerlo]], coming on as a substitute for [[Jonathan Wilmet]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thefinalball.com/jogo.php?id=1287892|publisher=footballzz.co.uk|title=KV Mechelen 3–1 Westerlo|accessdate=2011-02-12|language=}}</ref> He scored his first league goal for Mechelen in a 2–1 away victory against [[Lierse S.K.|Lierse]] on 8 April.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thefinalball.com/jogo.php?id=1678771|publisher=footballzz.co.uk|title=Lierse 1–2 KV Mechelen|accessdate=2011-04-08|language=}}</ref>
On 22 August 2011, Kabasele joined Bulgarian club [[PFC Ludogorets Razgrad|Ludogorets Razgrad]] on a three-year contract for an undisclosed fee.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.gong.bg/view_article.php?article_id=220993|publisher=gong.bg|title=Лудогорец взе младежки национал на Белгия|accessdate=2011-08-22|language=Bulgarian}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ludogorets.com/news_en.html?full_news=73|publisher=ludogorets.com|title=Belgian national youth player in Ludogorets’ offense|accessdate=2011-08-22|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120326204656/http://www.ludogorets.com/news_en.html?full_news=73|archivedate=2012-03-26|df=}}</ref> On 19 November 2011, he opened his account for Ludogorets, scoring a [[last-minute goal]] in a 2–0 home win over [[PFC Kaliakra Kavarna|Kaliakra Kavarna]] in an [[Bulgarian A Professional Football Group|A PFG]] match.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/players/christian-kabasele/53627/|publisher=soccerway.com|title=Christian Kabasele match log|accessdate=2012-12-22}}</ref>
On 16 August 2012, Kabasele rejoined his first team Eupen on a two-year contract.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.as-eupen.be/de/2012/08/16/christian-kabasele/|publisher=as-eupen.be|title=Christian Kabasele|accessdate=2012-08-27|language=German}}</ref>
On 1 July 2016 he signed for [[Premier League]] side [[Watford F.C.|Watford]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/36683381 |title=Troy Deeney, Isaac Success & Christian Kabasele agree Watford deals |publisher=BBC Sport |date=1 July 2016 |accessdate=9 January 2017}}</ref> He scored his first goal for Watford in a 3–1 defeat to [[West Bromwich Albion]] on 3 December 2016.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/38113785 |title=West Brom 3–1 Watford |publisher=BBC Sport |date=3 December 2016 |accessdate=9 January 2017}}</ref>
==International career== Kabasele was born in the Democratic Republic of the Congo, but moved to Belgium at a young age.<ref>http://www.wdsport.co.uk/2016/08/christian-kabasele-justifies-his-fathers-decision-to-uproot-and-leave-congo/</ref> Kabasele was named as part of the senior [[Belgium national football team|Belgium]] squad for [[UEFA Euro 2016]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/36417368 |title=Euro 2016: Full squads for every country |work=BBC Sport |publisher=BBC |date=1 June 2016 |accessdate=10 June 2016}}</ref> He made his debut for the national team in a friendly against the [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands]] on 9 November 2016.
In May 2018 he was named in Belgium's preliminary [[Belgium national football team|squad]] for the [[2018 World Cup]] in [[Russia]].<ref>{{cite web|title= World Cup 2018: Belgium announce initial 28-man squad for Russia| url= https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/world-cup/belgium-world-cup-squad-confirmed-russia-2018-nainggolan-hazard-de-bruyne-lukaku-a8361241.html%3Famp 2018}}</ref> However, he did not make the final 23.<ref>https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/amp/football/44353673</ref>
